NoUI Platform

**Member Self-Service Portal**

**& Application Lifecycle Architecture**

DERP Proof of Concept

February 2026

*DRAFT --- Working Architecture Document*

1\. Purpose and Demo Narrative Impact

The current POC design demonstrates NoUI's capabilities starting from a
pre-populated work queue. A benefits analyst claims a work item and the
system assembles the right workspace. This is powerful, but it begins
the story in the middle. The audience must accept on faith that the work
item *arrived somehow*.

This document extends the POC to show the complete lifecycle: a member
initiates retirement through a self-service portal, the system validates
and routes the application into the staff work queue, the analyst
processes it with full transparency into the member's digital
submission, and the member sees real-time progress. Every step writes to
and reads from the database. Nothing is pre-populated or simulated.

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **The New Demo Narrative**                                            |
|                                                                       |
| *\"Watch what happens when Robert Martinez decides to retire. He logs |
| into the member portal, sees his information pre-populated, completes |
| his application, and submits. Now switch to the analyst view ---      |
| there's the work item in the queue, with everything Robert submitted  |
| already structured and validated. The analyst verifies, calculates,   |
| and approves. Switch back to Robert's view --- he can see exactly     |
| where his application is in the process. No phone calls. No           |
| wondering. Complete transparency in both directions.\"*               |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

This transforms the POC from a demonstration of internal tooling into a
demonstration of end-to-end digital pension administration.

1.1 Relationship to Existing Architecture

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Architectural Relationship**                                        |
|                                                                       |
| *This document extends the Dynamic Workspace UX Architecture, the     |
| Roles & Workspace Architecture, the Service Retirement Process        |
| Definition, and the Member Context Hub POC Scope. It does not replace |
| any of them. The member portal is a new entry point into the same     |
| composition engine, the same rules engine, the same data layer. What  |
| is new: a member-facing interface, a digital application pipeline, a  |
| bidirectional status model, and the database mutations to support all |
| three.*                                                               |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

2\. POC Scope Boundaries

2.1 In Scope

  -------------------------- -------------------------------------------------
  **Capability**             **Description**

  Digital retirement         Member completes the equivalent of DERP's 4-page
  application                Retirement Application through a guided digital
                             form. Parts A, B, C, and G are fully functional.
                             Parts D, E, F, H are present but simplified.

  Smart pre-population       System pre-fills member information from
                             MEMBER_MASTER, beneficiary data from BENEFICIARY
                             table, employment dates from EMPLOYMENT_HIST.
                             Member confirms or corrects.

  Application-to-work-item   Submitted application creates a real CASE_HIST
  pipeline                   record, an APPLICATION_SUBMISSION record,
                             TRANSACTION_LOG entries, and routes to the
                             analyst queue.

  Bidirectional status       Member portal shows application progress through
  tracking                   defined stages. Staff actions advance the stage.
                             Both views read from the same CASE_HIST record.

  Staff workspace            Analyst's task workspace displays the digital
  integration                submission as structured data alongside the
                             calculated benefits. Staff can flag items needing
                             member action.

  Member communication       Staff can post status messages visible to the
                             member. Member can respond. Messages stored in
                             APPLICATION_MESSAGES table.

  Document checklist         System tracks which required documents have been
  tracking                   submitted. Checklist is visible to both member
                             and analyst.

  Database interactions      All operations perform real INSERT/UPDATE against
                             PostgreSQL. No mocked data flows.
  -------------------------- -------------------------------------------------

