  workflow                 not collect
  ------------------------ ----------------------------------------------

2.3 Key Design Decision: Notarization Boundary

DERP's retirement application **must be notarized**. This creates a
deliberate boundary in the digital workflow. The member portal allows
the member to complete all elections digitally, review and confirm their
choices, and generate a pre-filled PDF of the official application. The
member then prints, signs before a notary, and submits the notarized
copy. Once DERP staff receives the notarized document, they confirm it
in the system, which advances the application from **SUBMITTED_DIGITAL**
to **NOTARIZED_RECEIVED** status.

For the POC demo, we simulate this step with a single button click by
the analyst ("Confirm notarized application received"). The
architectural point is that the system models this real-world constraint
rather than pretending it doesn't exist.

3\. Retirement Application Form Mapping

The DERP Retirement Application is a 4-page paper form with 9 parts (A
through I). Each part maps to a specific step in the digital portal
experience and specific database fields. This section provides the
complete mapping.

3.1 Part A: Member Information

**Digital Experience:** Pre-populated from MEMBER_MASTER. Member reviews
and confirms or requests correction. Corrections are flagged for staff
review rather than directly modifying the legacy record.

  ---------------- ------------------------------ -------------------- -----------------
  **Form Field**   **Source Table.Column**        **Pre-populated?**   **Member
                                                                       Editable?**

  Name             MEMBER_MASTER.FIRST_NM,        Yes                  Request
                   MIDDLE_NM, LAST_NM                                  correction only

  DERP ID          MEMBER_MASTER.MBR_ID           Yes                  No (display only)

  Date of Birth    MEMBER_MASTER.DOB              Yes                  Request
                                                                       correction only

  Gender           MEMBER_MASTER.GENDER_CD        Yes                  Request
                                                                       correction only

  Social Security  MEMBER_MASTER.SSN (masked)     Yes (last 4 only)    No
  Number                                                               

  Effective Date   Calculated suggestion          Suggested            Yes (constrained)
  of Retirement                                                        

  Retirement Type  Auto-determined from rules     Yes                  No (computed)
                   engine                                              

  Residence        MEMBER_MASTER.ADDR_LINE1,      Yes                  Yes
  Address          CITY, etc.                                          

  Mailing Address  Same or separate               Yes                  Yes

  Phone Numbers    MEMBER_MASTER.HOME_PHONE,      Yes                  Yes
                   CELL_PHONE                                          

  Email Address    MEMBER_MASTER.EMAIL_ADDR       Yes                  Yes

  Marital Status   MEMBER_MASTER.MARITAL_STATUS   Yes                  Yes
                                                                       (certification)
  ---------------- ------------------------------ -------------------- -----------------

**Nuance --- Effective Date of Retirement:** The system suggests the
first day of the month following the member's stated last day of work,
per DERP rules. The portal explains that the benefit is effective the
first of the month after separation and that separating at month-end
maximizes service credit. This is an early demonstration of NoUI's rules
intelligence surfacing at the member level.

**Nuance --- Marital Status Certification:** The paper form requires the
member to affirm "I am married" or "I am not married." This is a legal
certification that may differ from what's on file. The digital form
captures this as an explicit affirmation that writes to the
APPLICATION_SUBMISSION record, not directly to MEMBER_MASTER. If the
certification differs from the system record, a flag is raised for staff
review.

3.2 Part B: Retirement Benefit Option Election

**Digital Experience:** The most consequential section. The portal
presents this as an interactive decision tool, not a form. The system
calculates all four payment option amounts in real time (using the rules
engine and the member's actual salary/service data) and displays them
side-by-side with clear explanations of trade-offs.

  --------------------- ------------------------ -------------------------
  **Election**          **Database Field**       **Validation Rules**

  Type 1: Maximum       APP_PAYMENT_OPTION =     If married, triggers
  Benefit               \'MAX\'                  spousal consent
                                                 requirement flag

  Type 2, Option 1:     APP_PAYMENT_OPTION =     Requires beneficiary
  100% J&S              \'JS100\'                designation

  Type 2, Option 2: 75% APP_PAYMENT_OPTION =     Requires beneficiary
  J&S                   \'JS075\'                designation

  Type 2, Option 3: 50% APP_PAYMENT_OPTION =     Requires beneficiary
  J&S                   \'JS050\'                designation; minimum for
                                                 married without consent

  Beneficiary Name      APP_BENE_NAME,           Required for all J&S
                        APP_BENE_SSN, etc.       options

  Beneficiary           APP_BENE_RELATIONSHIP    Required for all J&S
  Relationship                                   options

  Beneficiary DOB       APP_BENE_DOB             Required (affects
                                                 actuarial calculation)
  --------------------- ------------------------ -------------------------

**Nuance --- Irrevocability Warning:** The paper form states in bold:
"once retirement benefits begin, neither the selected benefit option,
nor the designated beneficiary, can ever be changed." The digital form
must present this prominently with an explicit acknowledgment checkbox
before the member can proceed. This acknowledgment is timestamped in
APPLICATION_SUBMISSION.IRREVOCABILITY_ACK_TS.

**Nuance --- Spousal Consent Logic:** If the member certifies they are
married (Part A) and selects either Maximum benefit OR a J&S option
naming someone other than their spouse, the system immediately flags
that a Spousal Consent at Retirement form will be required. The portal
displays this requirement clearly and generates a pre-filled Spousal
Consent form for the member to print and have their spouse sign before a
notary. The Spousal Consent form cannot be signed more than 90 days
before first payment per DERP rules.

**Nuance --- Beneficiary Predeceases Member:** The application states
that if the J&S beneficiary dies before the member, the benefit
increases to the Maximum amount and no new beneficiary can be selected.
The portal includes this disclosure during beneficiary designation.

3.3 Part C: Lump-Sum Death Benefit Election

**Digital Experience:** Conditional section that adapts based on the
member's retirement type. The system knows the retirement type from the
eligibility determination and pre-selects the appropriate category.

  ------------------- --------------------- ------------------------------
  **Retirement Type** **Death Benefit       **Portal Behavior**
                      Amount**              

  Normal / Rule of    \$5,000               Show amount, offer 50 or 100
  75/85                                     installment election

  Early Retirement,   \$5,000 minus         Calculate and show actual
  Tier 1/2            \$250/yr under 65     amount

  Early Retirement,   \$5,000 minus         Calculate and show actual
  Tier 3              \$500/yr under 65     amount

  Disability (pre-65) 150% of AMS, max      Out of scope for POC
                      \$50,000              

  Deferred Retirement Not eligible          Section hidden entirely
  ------------------- --------------------- ------------------------------

**Database Fields:** APP_DEATH_BENEFIT_AMT (calculated),
APP_DEATH_BENEFIT_ELECTION ('DRAW_50', 'DRAW_100', 'NO_DRAW'),
APP_DEATH_BENE_NAME, APP_DEATH_BENE_SSN, APP_DEATH_BENE_RELATIONSHIP.

**Nuance --- Installment Irrevocability:** Choosing 50 or 100
installments is irrevocable. The installment is paid at the same time as
the monthly retirement benefit. The portal must make this clear and
require explicit acknowledgment.

3.4 Part D: Direct Deposit Information

**Digital Experience (Simplified for POC):** Per DRMC §18-413(b)(2),
benefits must be paid by direct deposit. The actual DERP application
notes that if the member entered direct deposit information via the MSS
Portal, they don't need to attach a voided check. For the POC, we
present a simple bank account entry form (routing number, account
number, account type). This captures the data in APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
but does not integrate with a banking validation service.

**Database Fields:** APP_BANK_ROUTING, APP_BANK_ACCOUNT,
APP_BANK_ACCT_TYPE ('CHECKING', 'SAVINGS'). These fields are stored in
APPLICATION_SUBMISSION only, not written to a banking table.

3.5 Part E: Income Tax Withholding Election

**Digital Experience (Simplified for POC):** The portal presents the
three federal and three Colorado state withholding options as radio
buttons with explanatory text. The Colorado exclusion amounts
(\$24,000/year for 65+, \$20,000/year for 55-64) are displayed as
informational context. The system does not calculate withholding
amounts; it captures the election for staff processing.

**Database Fields:** APP_FED_TAX_ELECTION, APP_FED_TAX_FILING_STATUS,
APP_FED_TAX_ADDL_AMT, APP_FED_TAX_FIXED_AMT, APP_FED_TAX_FIXED_PCT,
APP_CO_TAX_ELECTION (mirror structure for Colorado). These use an ENUM
pattern: 'NONE', 'TABLE', 'FIXED'.

3.6 Part F: Electronic Communication

**Digital Experience:** Simple acknowledgment that direct deposit
advices and 1099-R forms are available electronically via MyDERP.org.
Single checkbox. Database field: APP_ELECTRONIC_COMM_ACK (boolean,
timestamped).

3.7 Part G: Medical/Dental/Vision Insurance Participation

**Digital Experience:** Critical for benefit calculation because it
determines IPR eligibility. The portal presents a clear explanation of
the IPR benefit: DERP contributes to insurance premiums based on years
of service and Medicare eligibility. If the member elects "Yes," the
system notes that a separate Health Insurance Election Form is required
and calculates the IPR amount for display. If "No," the system confirms
the member understands they can only enroll during Open Enrollment or
qualifying life events.

**Database Fields:** APP_INSURANCE_ELECTION ('YES', 'NO'). When 'YES',
the document checklist adds the Health Insurance Election Form as a
required item.

**Nuance --- IPR Calculation Display:** The system calculates and
displays the IPR amount during this step: \$6.25/year of service if
Medicare-eligible, \$12.50/year if not. For Robert Martinez (28.75
years, age 63, not Medicare-eligible): 28.75 × \$12.50 = \$359.38/month.
This shows the member the financial impact of their insurance decision.

3.8 Part H: Re-employment Acknowledgment

**Digital Experience:** Informational section with acknowledgment
checkbox. Displays the two key rules: 30-day minimum separation after
final payout, and 1,000-hour annual limit for re-employment with a
covered employer. Violation results in benefit suspension. Database
field: APP_REEMPLOY_ACK (boolean, timestamped).

3.9 Part I: Member Confirmation & Notarization

**Digital Experience:** The final step has two sub-parts. First, a
digital confirmation where the member reviews a complete summary of all
elections and acknowledgments, then confirms digitally. This creates a
timestamped record (APP_DIGITAL_CONFIRM_TS) with the member's portal
session ID. Second, the system generates a pre-filled PDF of the
official Retirement Application with all the member's elections
populated. The member is instructed to print, sign before a notary, and
submit the notarized copy to DERP via email, fax, or mail.

**The notarization step is the bridge between digital and physical.**
The digital submission creates the work item and begins preliminary
processing. The notarized document receipt advances the process to the
formal review stage. This dual-confirmation model accurately represents
the real DERP process while demonstrating the value of digital
pre-submission.

4\. Database Schema Additions

All new tables follow the legacy schema conventions established in the
existing database design. These tables are added to the legacy schema
(not a separate modern schema) because they represent data that a real
pension system would store alongside existing records.

4.1 APPLICATION_SUBMISSION

Primary table for digital retirement applications. One row per
submission. This is the digital equivalent of the paper form.

  ----------------------------- --------------- ---------------------------------
  **Column**                    **Type**        **Description**

  APP_ID                        SERIAL PK       Auto-increment application
                                                identifier

  MBR_ID                        VARCHAR(10) FK  Reference to MEMBER_MASTER

  CASE_ID                       INTEGER FK      Reference to CASE_HIST (created
                                                on submission)

  APP_STATUS                    VARCHAR(20)     DRAFT, SUBMITTED,
                                                NOTARIZED_RECEIVED, IN_REVIEW,
                                                APPROVED, DENIED

  APP_SUBMIT_TS                 TIMESTAMP       When member clicked submit

  APP_NOTARIZED_RECV_TS         TIMESTAMP       When staff confirmed notarized
                                                copy received

  EFF_RETIREMENT_DT             DATE            Elected effective date of
                                                retirement

  LAST_DAY_WORKED               DATE            Member's stated last day of
                                                employment

  RETIREMENT_TYPE               VARCHAR(20)     NORMAL, RULE_OF_75, RULE_OF_85,
                                                EARLY

  MARITAL_STATUS_CERT           VARCHAR(10)     MARRIED or NOT_MARRIED (legal
                                                certification)

  MARITAL_DIFF_FLAG             BOOLEAN         True if certification differs
                                                from MEMBER_MASTER

  APP_PAYMENT_OPTION            VARCHAR(10)     MAX, JS100, JS075, JS050

  APP_BENE_NAME                 VARCHAR(100)    J&S beneficiary full name

