4.2 APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS

Tracks required and received documents for each application. Drives the
document checklist visible to both member and staff.

  ---------------- ------------- ----------------------------------------
  **Column**       **Type**      **Description**

  DOC_ID           SERIAL PK     Auto-increment

  APP_ID           INTEGER FK    Reference to APPLICATION_SUBMISSION

  DOC_TYPE         VARCHAR(30)   BIRTH_CERT_MEMBER, BIRTH_CERT_SPOUSE,
                                 MARRIAGE_CERT, DIVORCE_DECREE,
                                 MEDICARE_CARD, SPOUSAL_CONSENT,
                                 INSURANCE_FORM, VOIDED_CHECK,
                                 NOTARIZED_APP, SSA_ESTIMATE

  DOC_REQUIRED     BOOLEAN       Whether this document is required for
                                 this application

  DOC_STATUS       VARCHAR(15)   PENDING, RECEIVED, WAIVED,
                                 NOT_APPLICABLE

  DOC_RECV_DT      DATE          Date document received by DERP

  DOC_RECV_BY      VARCHAR(30)   Staff member who logged receipt

  DOC_NOTES        TEXT          Notes about the document

  CREATE_DT        TIMESTAMP     Row creation timestamp
  ---------------- ------------- ----------------------------------------

**Document Requirements Logic:** When an application is submitted, the
system auto-generates the required document rows based on the member's
situation. Birth certificate is always required for the member. Marriage
certificate is required if married. Spousal consent is required if
married and electing Maximum or J&S with non-spouse. Medicare card is
required if age 65+. Health Insurance Election Form is required if
APP_INSURANCE_ELECTION = 'YES'. This logic runs in the intelligence
service using the same rules engine that drives workspace composition.

4.3 APPLICATION_MESSAGES

Bidirectional communication log between staff and member, scoped to a
specific application.

  --------------- ------------- ------------------------------------------
  **Column**      **Type**      **Description**

  MSG_ID          SERIAL PK     Auto-increment

  APP_ID          INTEGER FK    Reference to APPLICATION_SUBMISSION

  SENDER_TYPE     VARCHAR(10)   MEMBER or STAFF

  SENDER_ID       VARCHAR(30)   Member ID or staff user ID

  MSG_TEXT        TEXT          Message content

  MSG_TS          TIMESTAMP     When message was sent

  READ_TS         TIMESTAMP     When recipient read the message (null if
                                unread)

  MSG_TYPE        VARCHAR(20)   INFO, ACTION_REQUIRED, RESPONSE,
                                STATUS_UPDATE
  --------------- ------------- ------------------------------------------

4.4 APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY

Immutable log of every status change, providing the audit trail for the
application lifecycle.

  --------------- ------------- ------------------------------------------
  **Column**      **Type**      **Description**

  HIST_ID         SERIAL PK     Auto-increment

  APP_ID          INTEGER FK    Reference to APPLICATION_SUBMISSION

  OLD_STATUS      VARCHAR(20)   Previous status (null for initial
                                creation)

  NEW_STATUS      VARCHAR(20)   New status

  CHANGED_BY      VARCHAR(30)   Who triggered the change

  CHANGED_TS      TIMESTAMP     When the change occurred

  CHANGE_REASON   TEXT          Optional explanation
  --------------- ------------- ------------------------------------------

4.5 Modifications to Existing Tables

The existing CASE_HIST table is extended with one new column to link to
the digital application:

  ------------- ----------------------- --------------- ------------------------
  **Table**     **New Column**          **Type**        **Description**

  CASE_HIST     APP_ID                  INTEGER FK NULL Link to
                                                        APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
                                                        if originated from
                                                        portal

  CASE_HIST     MEMBER_VISIBLE_STATUS   VARCHAR(30)     Simplified status
                                                        visible to member in
                                                        portal

  CASE_HIST     MEMBER_STATUS_DETAIL    VARCHAR(200)    Human-readable status
                                                        description for member
  ------------- ----------------------- --------------- ------------------------

The TRANSACTION_LOG table requires no schema changes. Application events
are logged using the existing structure with TXN_TYPE values like
'APP_SUBMIT', 'APP_STATUS_CHG', 'APP_DOC_RECV', 'APP_MSG_SENT'.

5\. Application Lifecycle State Model

The application moves through defined states. Each state has an internal
representation (used by staff and system logic) and a member-facing
representation (simplified, non-technical language displayed in the
portal).

  -------------------- ----------------- ------------------------- ---------------
  **Internal Status**  **Member-Facing   **Member-Facing Detail**  **Triggered
                       Status**                                    By**

  DRAFT                In Progress       You're still working on   Member starts
                                         your application. It's    application
                                         saved automatically.      

  SUBMITTED            Submitted         We've received your       Member clicks
                                         digital application.      Submit
                                         Please print, sign before 
                                         a notary, and submit the  
                                         notarized copy.           

  NOTARIZED_RECEIVED   Under Review      We've received your       Staff confirms
                                         notarized application and receipt
                                         have started our review.  

  ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW   Under Review      We're verifying your      Staff begins
                                         eligibility for           processing
                                         retirement benefits.      

  CALCULATION          Benefit           We're calculating your    Eligibility
                       Calculation       retirement benefit based  confirmed
                                         on your service and       
                                         salary history.           

  PENDING_INFO         Action Needed     We need additional        Staff requests
                                         information from you.     info
                                         Please check your         
                                         messages.                 

  SUPERVISOR_REVIEW    Final Review      Your benefit calculation  Analyst submits
                                         is being reviewed by a    for review
                                         supervisor for final      
                                         approval.                 

  APPROVED             Approved          Your retirement           Supervisor
                                         application has been      approves
                                         approved! Your first      
                                         payment will be \[date\]. 

  DENIED               Denied            We were unable to approve Staff denies
                                         your application. Please  (rare)
                                         check your messages for   
                                         details.                  
  -------------------- ----------------- ------------------------- ---------------

5.1 State Transition Rules

State transitions are governed by the process orchestrator. The
following transitions are valid:

  -------------------- -------------------- --------------------- -------------
  **From**             **To**               **Condition**         **Actor**

  DRAFT                SUBMITTED            All required fields   Member
                                            complete, digital     
                                            confirmation signed   

  SUBMITTED            NOTARIZED_RECEIVED   Staff confirms        Staff
                                            physical receipt of   
                                            notarized application 

  NOTARIZED_RECEIVED   ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW   Work item claimed by  Staff
                                            analyst               

  ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW   CALCULATION          Eligibility           System +
                                            determination         Staff
                                            complete, all         
                                            criteria met          

  ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW   DENIED               Member does not meet  Staff
                                            eligibility           
                                            requirements          

  ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW   PENDING_INFO         Missing data or       Staff
                                            documents needed      

  CALCULATION          PENDING_INFO         Missing data or       Staff
                                            documents needed      

  CALCULATION          SUPERVISOR_REVIEW    Calculation complete, Staff
                                            all documents         
                                            received              

  PENDING_INFO         ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW   Member provides       System
                                            requested information 

  PENDING_INFO         CALCULATION          Member provides       System
                                            requested information 
                                            (if already past      
                                            eligibility)          

  SUPERVISOR_REVIEW    APPROVED             Supervisor approves   Supervisor

  SUPERVISOR_REVIEW    CALCULATION          Supervisor returns    Supervisor
                                            with corrections      

  Any                  DRAFT                Not valid             ---
                                            (submissions are      
                                            permanent)            
  -------------------- -------------------- --------------------- -------------

5.2 Progress Indicator for Member Portal

The member portal displays a simplified progress bar with these stages.
The internal state maps to a progress percentage and a highlighted step:

  ---------- ------------------ --------------------- --------------------
  **Portal   **Label**          **Internal States**   **Progress**
  Step**                                              

  1          Application        SUBMITTED             20%
             Submitted                                

  2          Notarized Copy     NOTARIZED_RECEIVED    35%
             Received                                 

  3          Eligibility        ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW    50%
             Verification                             

  4          Benefit            CALCULATION           70%
             Calculation                              

  5          Final Review       SUPERVISOR_REVIEW     85%

  6          Approved           APPROVED              100%
  ---------- ------------------ --------------------- --------------------

PENDING_INFO overlays on the current step with an alert badge rather
than advancing/retreating the progress bar. The member sees the progress
bar at its last position plus an "Action Needed" indicator.

6\. Member Portal Architecture

6.1 Portal Entry Point and Authentication

**For the POC:** Simulated authentication. The portal login screen
offers a dropdown of the four demo case members (Robert Martinez,
Jennifer Kim, David Washington, and Robert Martinez as a DRO variant).
Selecting a member loads their portal session. No real authentication
provider is integrated.

**Architectural note:** In production, the member portal would integrate
with the agency's identity provider (Active Directory, SAML, or the
existing MyDERP.org authentication). The portal interface is designed as
a standalone React application that communicates with the NoUI backend
through the same API layer the staff interfaces use, with RBAC
restricting the member to their own data.

6.2 Portal Navigation Structure

The member portal has three views for the POC:

  ---------------- ------------------- ----------------------------------
  **View**         **Purpose**         **Key Components**

  Dashboard        Landing page after  Welcome message, retirement
                   login               readiness summary, application
                                       status card (if in progress),
                                       quick actions

  Retirement       Guided multi-step   Step-by-step wizard with
  Application      form                save/resume, pre-populated fields,
                                       real-time validation, payment
                                       option calculator

  Application      Track submitted     Progress bar, status detail,
  Status           application         message thread, document checklist
  ---------------- ------------------- ----------------------------------

6.3 Retirement Application Wizard

The digital application is presented as a multi-step wizard. Steps map
to the paper form parts but are reorganized for a better digital
experience. The member can navigate forward and backward freely; data is
auto-saved to a DRAFT application record on every field change.

  ---------- ------------------ ------------------ ----------------------------
  **Step**   **Title**          **Maps to Form     **Key Interactions**
                                Part(s)**          

  1          Verify Your        Part A             Review pre-populated data,
             Information                           confirm or request
                                                   corrections, certify marital
                                                   status

  2          Choose Your        Part B             Interactive payment option
             Benefit Option                        comparison with calculated
                                                   amounts, beneficiary entry
                                                   if J&S, spousal consent
                                                   flagging

  3          Death Benefit      Part C             Calculated amount shown,
             Election                              installment choice, death
                                                   benefit beneficiary

  4          Payment & Tax      Parts D, E         Direct deposit entry, tax
             Setup                                 withholding elections with
                                                   guidance

  5          Health Insurance   Part G             Insurance election with IPR
                                                   calculation display

  6          Acknowledgments    Parts F, H         Electronic communication and
                                                   re-employment
                                                   acknowledgments

  7          Review & Submit    Part I             Complete summary, final
                                                   confirmation, PDF generation
  ---------- ------------------ ------------------ ----------------------------

**Auto-Save Behavior:** Every field change triggers a debounced save
(500ms delay) to the APPLICATION_SUBMISSION table via PATCH
/api/v1/portal/applications/{id}. The member can close the browser and
resume later. The DRAFT status persists until explicit submission.

**Validation Strategy:** Field-level validation runs on blur (format,
required). Step-level validation runs on "Continue" (cross-field rules
like "beneficiary required if J&S selected"). Submission validation runs
the full rules engine to verify eligibility and completeness before
allowing final submit.

7\. API Specifications

All portal APIs follow the existing NoUI API conventions (JSON
request/response, consistent error format, request_id in meta). Portal
APIs are prefixed with /api/v1/portal/ and are restricted by RBAC to the
authenticated member's own data.

7.1 Member Portal APIs

  ------------ -------------------------------------------------- ------------------- -----------------------------
  **Method**   **Endpoint**                                       **Description**     **Database Effect**

  GET          /api/v1/portal/member/profile                      Pre-populated       SELECT from MEMBER_MASTER,
                                                                  member info for     EMPLOYMENT_HIST, BENEFICIARY
                                                                  application         

  GET          /api/v1/portal/member/retirement-readiness         Eligibility         Rules engine evaluation
                                                                  summary, estimated  against member data
                                                                  benefit             

  POST         /api/v1/portal/applications                        Create new draft    INSERT into
                                                                  application         APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
                                                                                      (DRAFT), INSERT into
                                                                                      CASE_HIST

  GET          /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}                   Retrieve            SELECT from
                                                                  application (draft  APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
                                                                  or submitted)       

  PATCH        /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}                   Auto-save field     UPDATE
                                                                  updates to draft    APPLICATION_SUBMISSION,
                                                                                      INSERT TRANSACTION_LOG

  POST         /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}/submit            Submit completed    UPDATE status to SUBMITTED,
                                                                  application         INSERT
                                                                                      APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY,
                                                                                      INSERT APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS,
                                                                                      INSERT TRANSACTION_LOG,
                                                                                      trigger work item routing

  GET          /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}/status            Current status with SELECT from CASE_HIST,
                                                                  member-facing       APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY
                                                                  detail              

  GET          /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}/documents         Document checklist  SELECT from
                                                                  with statuses       APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS

  GET          /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}/messages          Message thread for  SELECT from
                                                                  this application    APPLICATION_MESSAGES

  POST         /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}/messages          Send message to     INSERT into
                                                                  staff               APPLICATION_MESSAGES, INSERT
                                                                                      TRANSACTION_LOG

  GET          /api/v1/portal/applications/{id}/benefit-options   Calculate all       Rules engine calculation
                                                                  payment option      (read-only against
                                                                  amounts             salary/service data)
  ------------ -------------------------------------------------- ------------------- -----------------------------

7.2 Staff-Side APIs (Additions)

  ------------ ---------------------------------------------- ------------------- -----------------------------------
  **Method**   **Endpoint**                                   **Description**     **Database Effect**

  GET          /api/v1/cases/{id}/application                 Retrieve linked     SELECT from APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
                                                              digital application WHERE CASE_ID = {id}

  POST         /api/v1/cases/{id}/confirm-notarized           Confirm notarized   UPDATE APP_STATUS,
                                                              document received   APP_NOTARIZED_RECV_TS; INSERT
                                                                                  APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY,
                                                                                  TRANSACTION_LOG

  POST         /api/v1/cases/{id}/request-info                Send info request   UPDATE APP_STATUS to PENDING_INFO,
                                                              to member           INSERT APPLICATION_MESSAGES,
                                                                                  APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY

  POST         /api/v1/cases/{id}/advance-stage               Move to next        UPDATE APP_STATUS, CASE_HIST;
                                                              processing stage    INSERT APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY,
                                                                                  TRANSACTION_LOG

  POST         /api/v1/cases/{id}/documents/{docId}/receive   Mark document as    UPDATE
                                                              received            APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS.DOC_STATUS,
                                                                                  DOC_RECV_DT; INSERT TRANSACTION_LOG

  POST         /api/v1/cases/{id}/messages                    Send message to     INSERT APPLICATION_MESSAGES; INSERT
                                                              member              TRANSACTION_LOG
