8\. Application-to-Work-Item Pipeline

When a member submits their application, the system executes the
following pipeline. Every step writes to the database.

8.1 Submission Pipeline Steps

  ---------- ------------------------------------------ --------------------------------------------
  **Step**   **Action**                                 **Tables Affected**

  1          Validate application completeness (all     None (validation only)
             required fields, all acknowledgments)      

  2          Update APPLICATION_SUBMISSION.APP_STATUS   APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
             from DRAFT to SUBMITTED                    

  3          Insert APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY row      APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY
             (DRAFT → SUBMITTED)                        

  4          Determine retirement type via rules engine APPLICATION_SUBMISSION.RETIREMENT_TYPE
             (NORMAL, RULE_OF_75, RULE_OF_85, EARLY)    

  5          Calculate required documents based on      APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS (batch INSERT)
             member situation and elections             

  6          Evaluate spousal consent requirement       APPLICATION_SUBMISSION.SPOUSAL_CONSENT_REQ

  7          Create CASE_HIST work item (type=SVC_RET,  CASE_HIST
             status=OPEN, priority=calculated)          

  8          Link application to case: update           CASE_HIST, APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
             CASE_HIST.APP_ID and                       
             APPLICATION_SUBMISSION.CASE_ID             

  9          Set member-visible status on case          CASE_HIST.MEMBER_VISIBLE_STATUS,
                                                        MEMBER_STATUS_DETAIL

  10         Log submission event                       TRANSACTION_LOG

  11         Determine routing: assign to queue based   CASE_HIST.ASSIGNED_TO (queue, not
             on tier, DRO presence, complexity          individual)
  ---------- ------------------------------------------ --------------------------------------------

8.2 Routing Rules

For the POC, routing is deterministic (Tier 1). Work items are assigned
to a general benefits analyst queue. The following routing signals are
computed and stored on the case for future intelligent routing:

  ------------------ ----------------------- ------------------------------
  **Signal**         **Source**              **Impact**

  Tier complexity    Member's tier from hire Tier 1 members have leave
                     date                    payout, longer histories

  DRO present        DRO_MASTER check        Cases with DRO require
                                             additional calculation steps

  Early retirement   Eligibility evaluation  Requires reduction
                                             calculation, threshold
                                             proximity check

  Purchased service  SVC_CREDIT check        Must verify exclusion from
                                             Rule of 75/85

  Document           APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS   Cases with all documents ready
  completeness                               are prioritized

  Processing         15th-of-month cutoff    Cases close to cutoff get
  deadline proximity                         priority boost
  ------------------ ----------------------- ------------------------------

8.3 Priority Calculation

Priority is stored as an integer on CASE_HIST.PRIORITY (1 = highest).
For the POC, priority is computed as: base priority of 3, minus 1 if
processing deadline is within 5 business days, minus 1 if all documents
are received (case is ready to work), plus 1 if in PENDING_INFO state
(waiting on member, not actionable). This simple model demonstrates the
concept; production would use the full intelligent prioritization
described in the Dynamic Workspace UX Architecture.

9\. Staff Workspace Integration

When an analyst opens a work item that originated from the portal, the
workspace composition includes additional components that display the
digital submission. This is a Tier 2 composition rule: IF case.APP_ID IS
NOT NULL, include digital application components.

9.1 New Workspace Components

  --------------------------- --------------------------- -----------------------------------
  **Component**               **Purpose**                 **Data Source**

  DigitalApplicationSummary   Displays all member         APPLICATION_SUBMISSION
                              elections from the portal   
                              submission in a structured, 
                              print-ready format          

  DocumentChecklist           Interactive checklist       APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS
                              showing required/received   
                              documents with ability to   
                              mark received               

  ApplicationTimeline         Visual timeline of all      APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY
                              status changes with         
                              timestamps and actors       

  MemberMessages              Communication thread with   APPLICATION_MESSAGES
                              ability to send messages    
                              and info requests           

  NotarizationConfirmation    Prominent action button to  APPLICATION_SUBMISSION.APP_STATUS
                              confirm receipt of          
                              notarized application       
                              (shown only when status =   
                              SUBMITTED)                  
  --------------------------- --------------------------- -----------------------------------

9.2 Workspace Composition Rules

The composition engine evaluates the application status to determine
which components appear and in what order:

  -------------------- ------------------------------ ----------------------
  **Application        **Additional Components**      **Component Order
  Status**                                            Priority**

  SUBMITTED (awaiting  NotarizationConfirmation       Notarization action
  notarized)           (prominent),                   first
                       DigitalApplicationSummary,     
                       DocumentChecklist              

  NOTARIZED_RECEIVED   DigitalApplicationSummary,     Standard processing
                       DocumentChecklist,             order
                       MemberMessages                 

  ELIGIBILITY_REVIEW   DigitalApplicationSummary      Eligibility components
                       (collapsed),                   primary
                       DocumentChecklist, standard    
                       eligibility components         

  CALCULATION          DigitalApplicationSummary      Calculation components
                       (collapsed),                   primary
                       BenefitCalculationPanel        
                       (primary),                     
                       PaymentOptionsComparison       

  PENDING_INFO         MemberMessages (prominent,     Communication first
                       with compose open),            
                       DocumentChecklist,             
                       pending-reason indicator       

  SUPERVISOR_REVIEW    Full case summary in read-only Approval actions
                       mode with                      primary
                       approve/reject/return actions  
  -------------------- ------------------------------ ----------------------

**Key insight:** The digital application data enables a qualitatively
different analyst experience. Instead of transcribing from a scanned
PDF, the analyst sees structured, validated data they can
cross-reference against the system record. Discrepancies (like marital
status differences) are flagged automatically. The analyst focuses on
verification and judgment, not data entry.

10\. Demo Case Integration

Each of the four demo cases gets a specific demo script showing the
portal-to-staff lifecycle. The primary walkthrough uses Case 1 (Robert
Martinez). Cases 2--4 demonstrate variations.

