10.2 Case 2: Jennifer Kim --- Scenario Modeling in Portal

Jennifer's case demonstrates a critical portal feature: the benefit
option display shows her early retirement reduction (30%,
\$1,633.07/month) alongside a callout: **"If you wait until age 56,
you'll meet the Rule of 75 and receive approximately \$2,518/month with
no reduction --- a 54% increase."** This is the scenario modeler
surfaced in the member portal. The system knows Jennifer is 0.83 points
from the Rule of 75 threshold because it ran the rules engine against
her data. This is a uniquely powerful POC moment: the system proactively
helps members make better decisions.

10.3 Case 3: David Washington --- Tier 3 Differences

David's portal experience highlights Tier 3 differences: the 60-month
AMS window (versus 36 for Tiers 1/2), the Rule of 85 instead of Rule of
75, the 6% per year early retirement reduction instead of 3%, and the
higher death benefit reduction (\$500/year instead of \$250). The portal
adapts all calculations and explanatory text to his tier automatically.

10.4 Case 4: Robert Martinez with DRO --- DRO Awareness

When Robert (DRO variant) logs into the portal, the system detects the
DRO record in DRO_MASTER and adds a prominent informational banner: **"A
Domestic Relations Order is on file for your account. Your retirement
benefit will be divided per the court order. The amounts shown below
reflect your portion after the DRO division."** The payment option
amounts shown in Step 2 reflect the post-DRO member share. This requires
the portal's benefit calculation endpoint to integrate with the DRO
calculation logic already built for the staff workspace.

11\. Technical Implementation Notes for Claude Code

11.1 Frontend Architecture

The member portal is a separate route tree within the existing React
application, not a separate deployment. It shares the component library,
design system, and API client but has its own layout shell and
navigation. The route structure:

  --------------------- ----------------------------- -------------------------
  **Route**             **Component**                 **Auth Requirement**

  /portal               PortalLayout (shell)          Member session

  /portal/dashboard     MemberDashboard               Member session

  /portal/apply         RetirementApplicationWizard   Member session + active
                                                      status

  /portal/apply/:id     RetirementApplicationWizard   Member session + owns
                        (resume)                      application

  /portal/status/:id    ApplicationStatus             Member session + owns
                                                      application

  /staff/\*             Existing staff routes         Staff session (existing)
  --------------------- ----------------------------- -------------------------

11.2 Backend Service Changes

Portal APIs are added to the existing service architecture. The
connector service handles database reads/writes. The intelligence
service handles rules evaluation and routing. The workspace service
handles portal composition logic. No new services are introduced.

  -------------- ---------------------------- ---------------------------------
  **Service**    **New Endpoints**            **New Logic**

  Connector      CRUD for                     Standard database access patterns
                 APPLICATION_SUBMISSION,      following existing conventions
                 APPLICATION_DOCUMENTS,       
                 APPLICATION_MESSAGES,        
                 APPLICATION_STATUS_HISTORY   

  Intelligence   Benefit option calculation   Reuses existing rules engine;
                 for portal, routing rules,   adds portal-facing response
                 document requirement         formatting
                 generation                   

  Workspace      Portal composition endpoint  Tier-aware step adaptation (which
                 for application wizard step  fields/explanations to show based
                 configuration                on member tier)
  -------------- ---------------------------- ---------------------------------

11.3 Data Generation Updates

The generate_derp_data.py script is extended to create pre-seeded
application data for demo cases. For Cases 2, 3, and 4, applications
exist in various lifecycle states to demonstrate the status tracking
view without requiring live submission during every demo. Case 1 (Robert
Martinez) is left **without** a pre-existing application so the full
submission flow can be demonstrated live.

  ------------------- ------------------- -------------------------------
  **Demo Case**       **Pre-Seeded        **Demo Purpose**
                      Application State** 

  Case 1: Robert      No application      Live full-lifecycle walkthrough
  Martinez            (clean slate)       

  Case 2: Jennifer    SUBMITTED (awaiting Show portal status view,
  Kim                 notarized)          scenario callout

  Case 3: David       CALCULATION         Show progress bar at 70%, Tier
  Washington          (mid-processing)    3 differences

  Case 4: Robert      No application      Live submission showing DRO
  Martinez DRO        (clean slate)       awareness
  ------------------- ------------------- -------------------------------

12\. Security Considerations

The member portal introduces a new attack surface and a new user type.
The following security controls apply, consistent with the NoUI Security
Architecture.

  ------------------ --------------------------- -------------------------
  **Concern**        **Control**                 **POC Implementation**

  Member can only    RBAC: portal role restricts Enforced at API layer;
  see own data       all queries to WHERE MBR_ID all queries parameterized
                     = authenticated_member      

  Member cannot      Portal writes only to       Separate write
  modify legacy      APPLICATION\_\* tables;     permissions per table
  records            MEMBER_MASTER is read-only  
                     from portal                 

  SSN handling       SSN displayed as masked     Backend masks before
                     (\*\*\*-\*\*-1234); full    serialization
                     SSN never sent to portal    
                     frontend                    

  Beneficiary SSN in Encrypted at rest in        AES-256 column-level
  application        APPLICATION_SUBMISSION;     encryption
                     decrypted only for staff    
                     view                        

  Session security   POC: simulated sessions.    Session tokens with
                     Production: integrate with  member ID binding
                     agency IdP                  

  Audit trail        All portal actions logged   Follows existing
                     to TRANSACTION_LOG with     transaction logging
                     session ID and IP           pattern

  Rate limiting      Submission endpoint limited POC: basic rate limit;
                     to prevent abuse            production: full WAF
  ------------------ --------------------------- -------------------------

13\. What This Document Is Not

This document does not define the visual design of the member portal.
Visual design follows the NoUI Design System and the Dynamic Workspace
UX Architecture.

This document does not define how the benefit calculation works.
Calculation logic is defined in the rules engine and validated against
the four demo case hand calculations.

This document does not replace the Service Retirement Process
Definition. That document defines the complete process stages. This
document adds the portal as an input channel to Stage 1 (Application
Intake).

This document does not define production authentication. POC
authentication is simulated. Production authentication architecture will
be defined when a real agency deployment is planned.

*End of Document*
